        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 11 at 4:18PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>At 417 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Lindsay, or 21 miles northwest of Glendive, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lambert, Lindsay, Bloomfield, Midway, and Enid.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
